    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-10T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-10T15:00:00-05:00" n="625"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d625">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">840.6363/7–1045: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 625<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Representative on the Allied Commission on
                        Reparations</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PEW1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Pauley</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Deputy Petroleum Administrator for
                        War</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_DRK1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Davies</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="1" xml:id="d625fn1">Sent to the Acting Secretary of State
                        over the signature of <persName corresp="#p_HK1">Harriman</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">urgent</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-10T23:00:00+03:00"
                            >July 10, 1945—11 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2503. From <persName corresp="#p_PEW1">Pauley</persName> to <persName
                        corresp="#p_DRK1">Davies</persName>, Petroleum <gloss target="#t_admin1"
                        >Admin</gloss> for War; copy to <persName corresp="#p_WJR1">Wolf</persName>,
                    White House.</p>
                <p>Reference your letter June 29<note n="2" xml:id="d625fn2">Not printed. For a
                        telegraphic summary, see <ref target="#d622">document No. 622</ref>.</note>
                    subject western and Mediterranean Europe oil requirements from Anglo-American
                    sources. Please rush <gloss target="#t_info1">info</gloss> tanker requirements
                    for this supply and approximate tanker saving in case Austrian, Hungarian and
                    Rumanian sources could be used fully according to figures submitted.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
